# Pix2Pix GAN — Satellite-to-Map Translation

## Setup

```bash
pip install torch torchvision numpy matplotlib pillow opencv-python
```

## Dataset (optional)
Place paired images in:
```
data/satellite/   ← input images
data/map/         ← target images
```
> If folders are missing, synthetic data is used automatically for demo purposes.

## Run

```bash
python pix2pix.py
```

## Outputs

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `sample.jpg` | Input, generated, and ground-truth map side-by-side |
| `training_loss_curves.png` | Generator vs Discriminator loss over epochs |
| `pixel_distribution.png` | Pixel intensity: real vs generated images |